mment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"nemin","user_is_author":false,"tags":["formalmethods"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ymnnmv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ymnnmv/introduction_formal_verification_with"},{"short_id":"oqi98d","created_at":"2026-07-19T09:39:59.496-05:00","title":"I Built an Even Better Ropebot Dog","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GFLa1b1juUo","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"briankung","user_is_author":false,"tags":["hardware","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oqi98d","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oqi98d/i_built_even_better_ropebot_dog"},{"short_id":"ukyvbo","created_at":"2026-07-19T09:32:11.914-05:00","title":"CodeSizer: Why is that binary so big?","url":"https://github.com/Wren6991/CodeSizer","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jeanthomas","user_is_author":false,"tags":["performance"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ukyvbo","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ukyvbo/codesizer_why_is_binary_so_big"},{"short_id":"t56kjo","created_at":"2026-07-19T09:28:24.625-05:00","title":"ZTA: Zero Token Architecture","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7WFt2JQ5sg","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"tomas","user_is_author":false,"tags":["vibecoding","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/t56kjo","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/t56kjo/zta_zero_token_architecture"},{"short_id":"jdcxr0","created_at":"2026-07-19T09:02:59.178-05:00","title":"Git email patch review addon for Thunderbird","url":"https://mccd.space/git/thunderbird-patch-review/file/README.html.html","score":10,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"mccd","user_is_author":true,"tags":["email","show","vcs","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jdcxr0","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jdcxr0/git_email_patch_review_addon_for"},{"short_id":"fq2z79","created_at":"2026-07-19T08:21:02.756-05:00","title":"Shake Blog","url":"https://abhin4v.github.io/shake-blog/","score":9,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"abhin4v","user_is_author":true,"tags":["haskell","release"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fq2z79","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fq2z79/shake_blog"},{"short_id":"69mche","created_at":"2026-07-19T08:14:39.350-05:00","title":"What is your favorite blog to read recently?","url":"","score":47,"flags":0,"comment_count":24,"description":"\u003cp\u003eEspecially interesting what it adds beyond an academic paper would.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Especially interesting what it adds beyond an academic paper would.","submitter_user":"oceanhaiyang","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/69mche","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/69mche/what_is_your_favorite_blog_read_recently"},{"short_id":"xhjzmc","created_at":"2026-07-19T07:41:16.574-05:00","title":"Skred is now a MIDI aware synth and drum machine construction kit","url":"","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://youtu.be/c6hJb0CYRmo?si=FhJRNCzNSdtMAiC-\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://youtu.be/c6hJb0CYRmo?si=FhJRNCzNSdtMAiC-\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis video has a step-by-step demo of using Skred v0.50.0 as a synth and drum machine construction kit.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe video shows a little of MIDI connection stuff too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor a MIDI \"keyboard\" here, I used a program called VMPK since it's on-screen and show what I hit versus how if affects Skred, but a real attached MIDI input device works too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSkred works on Linux, macOS, and MSWindows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere are precompiled versions of the CLI livecoding shell on GitHub under username octetta and repo pulp... look at the releases there for SKRED 0.50.0 to match functionality shown here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/octetta/pulp\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/octetta/pulp\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMIT / open source\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTimecodes...\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e0:00 Start Skred and test audio/Skope\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e0:43 Create a basic saw wave synth voice\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1:52 Setup MIDI and use VMPK as the input\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3:32 Fatten the synth with an additional square wave\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e4:49 Detune the voices\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e5:43 Add glide to one of the voices\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e6:40 Show the delay line per \"track\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e8:44 Add \"calculator\" drums via k-synth\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e9:50 Create a basic kick/snare drum pattern\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e10:32 Add delay to the drum sounds\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e14:08 All together and DONE\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e(I added an APL tag to this because I have a little version of a K-like language inside skred to make drum sounds... the demo loads two of these, although the source doesn't show up during load)\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"https://youtu.be/c6hJb0CYRmo?si=FhJRNCzNSdtMAiC-\r\n\r\nThis video has a step-by-step demo of using Skred v0.50.0 as a synth and drum machine construction kit. \r\n\r\nThe video shows a little of MIDI connection stuff too.\r\n\r\nFor a MIDI \"keyboard\" here, I used a program called VMPK since it's on-screen and show what I hit versus how if affects Skred, but a real attached MIDI input device works too.\r\n\r\nSkred works on Linux, macOS, and MSWindows.\r\n\r\nThere are precompiled versions of the CLI livecoding shell on GitHub under username octetta and repo pulp... look at the releases there for SKRED 0.50.0 to match functionality shown here.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/octetta/pulp\r\n\r\nMIT / open source\r\n\r\nTimecodes...\r\n\r\n0:00 Start Skred and test audio/Skope\r\n\r\n0:43 Create a basic saw wave synth voice\r\n\r\n1:52 Setup MIDI and use VMPK as the input\r\n\r\n3:32 Fatten the synth with an additional square wave\r\n\r\n4:49 Detune the voices\r\n\r\n5:43 Add glide to one of the voices\r\n\r\n6:40 Show the delay line per \"track\"\r\n\r\n8:44 Add \"calculator\" drums via k-synth\r\n\r\n9:50 Create a basic kick/snare drum pattern\r\n\r\n10:32 Add delay to the drum sounds\r\n\r\n14:08 All together and DONE\r\n\r\n(I added an APL tag to this because I have a little version of a K-like language inside skred to make drum sounds... the demo loads two of these, although the source doesn't show up during load)","submitter_user":"octetta","user_is_author":true,"tags":["apl","c","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/xhjzmc","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/xhjzmc/skred_is_now_midi_aware_synth_drum_machine"},{"short_id":"y8okbv","created_at":"2026-07-19T06:43:23.029-05:00","title":"Triton language for Alibaba SAIL","url":"https://github.com/t-head/triton-for-sail","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"sanxiyn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","compilers","hardware"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/y8okbv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/y8okbv/triton_language_for_alibaba_sail"},{"short_id":"k6ph7c","created_at":"2026-07-19T05:40:29.176-05:00","title":"The death and rebirth of my home server","url":"https://sgt.hootr.club/blog/home-server-rebirth/","score":18,"flags":0,"comment_count":4,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"steinuil","user_is_author":true,"tags":["linux","nix"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/k6ph7c","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/k6ph7c/death_rebirth_my_home_server"},{"short_id":"s4xsfz","created_at":"2026-07-19T04:59:51.525-05:00","title":"Follow the money, especially in open source","url":"https://www.osnews